Taking bets on when ISO C will acquire a form of templates, or taking it in even more generic direction - parametrized namespaces. Something like this (an illustrative example, don't knock me down for including <i>val</i> into <i>list</i>):<p><pre><code>  namespace(T)
  {
    struct list
    {
       T      val;
       list * next;
       list * prev;
    };

    void append(list * l, list * i)
    {
      ...
    }
  }
</code></pre>
Then<p><pre><code>  list<int> * foo, * bar;
  ...
  append(foo, bar);
</code></pre>
No need for namespace nesting, default arguments and other ++isms. Just something to replace multi-line macro blocks.
